# SCM (Smart Contacts Manager) 

This project is a **Smart Contacts Manager (SCM)** system built with **Spring Boot**. It provides functionality to manage users, contacts, and various other SCM-related entities. The system includes features such as user registration, user management, and more.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)


## Features

- **User Management**: Create, read, update, and delete (CRUD) operations for users.
- **Contact Management**: Manage user contacts with one-to-many relationships.
- **Authentication**: User authentication and authorization with roles.
- **Profile Management**: Users can manage their profile information.
- **Dark Mode**: Theme switching between light and dark mode.
- **Exception Handling**: Custom exception handling for resource not found scenarios.

## Technologies Used

- **Spring Boot**: For building the backend services.
- **Thymeleaf**: For server-side rendering of web pages.
- **Lombok**: To reduce boilerplate code (getters, setters, constructors, etc.).
- **H2 Database**: In-memory database for testing and development.
- **SLF4J with Logback**: For logging.
- **Flowbite**: For UI components and styling.
- **Font Awesome**: For icons.
